  <static seed="194" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring480.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{49x^{4}-64y^{4}}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left(7x^{2}+8y^{2}\right)\mathopen{}\left(7x^{2}-8y^{2}\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>Note that the given expression is the <em>difference of squares</em></p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
                {49x^{4}-64y^{4}} \amp  = ({7x^{2}})^2-({8y^{2}})^2\\
                            \amp  = {\left(7x^{2}+8y^{2}\right)\mathopen{}\left(7x^{2}-8y^{2}\right)}
            \end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>Note that this answer can be checked by using the FOIL (<alert>F</alert>irst <alert>O</alert>utside <alert>I</alert>nside <alert>L</alert>ast) technique (exercise).</p>
</solution>
